            <bug_when>2011-06-03 14:58:23 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>When running a demo in Demobrowser, the &quot;Run&quot; button changes to &quot;Stop&quot; until 
the demo has finished loading/rendering. The changing between the &quot;Run&quot; and 
&quot;Stop&quot; label makes the tool bar appear to &quot;shiver&quot; in FF 3.6, which gives a 
weird impression.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>25027</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2011-06-09 15:54:41 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Both buttons already have a common minWidth of 60px which isn&#39;t enough if the browser uses a larger than default font, as was the case with Thomas&#39; Firefox. I changed this so the calculated width of the &quot;stop&quot; button (the wider of the two) is used as the minWidth for both. This avoids the flickering for any font size.

Fixed with r27618.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
